text.tspan: Injury rate from mass movements, World
Injury rates are measured as the number of people injured per 100,000. A dry mass movement refers to a
landslide or rockfall which is not triggered by surface or subsurface water flows.
Note: Data includes disasters recorded up to October 2025.
